---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TypingAnimation from '../components/TypingAnimation.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Johnathan (Jack) Corbin | Robotics PhD @ Georgia Tech">
  <div class="page-container">
    <section class="hero">
      <h1 class="hero-name">Johnathan (Jack) Corbin</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Robotics PhD Student · Georgia Institute of Technology
      </p>
      <p class="hero-typing">
        Researching <TypingAnimation />
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section panel intro">
      <h2>// welcome</h2>
      <p>
        I'm a Robotics PhD student at Georgia Tech in the Daniel Guggenheim School of
        Aerospace Engineering. My research focuses on multi-agent control and safety —
        developing algorithms that let teams of autonomous systems operate together without
        colliding or violating constraints.
        <a href="/about">more about me →</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="section panel explainer">
      <h2>// background_simulation</h2>
      <p>
        The particles behind this page are running a <strong>Control Barrier Function (CBF)</strong>
        simulation — the same math I use to keep teams of robots from colliding.
        <span class="desktop-only">Move your cursor to become an obstacle.</span>
        <span class="mobile-only">The virtual obstacle orbiting the screen demonstrates this in action.</span>
        <a href="/research">learn more →</a>
      </p>
      <details class="cbf-details">
        <summary>$ cat cbf_details.txt</summary>
        <div class="details-content">
          <p>Each particle is an <strong>agent</strong> with a velocity vector. A
          <strong>Control Barrier Function</strong> h(x) = ‖x - x_obs‖ - R_safe
          defines a safe set around the obstacle (your cursor).</p>
          <p>The safety constraint <code>∂h/∂x · v ≥ -αh</code> ensures agents
          decelerate before breaching the barrier. When the constraint is violated,
          a minimal corrective velocity is applied along the obstacle-to-agent
          direction — guaranteeing safety with minimal deviation from the
          agent's desired trajectory.</p>
          <p>Parameters: <code>R_safe = 120px</code>, <code>α = 2.0</code>,
          <code>agents = 40</code> (20 on mobile).</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>// recent_news</h2>
      <ul class="news-list">
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2026.08]</span>
          Received MS in Aerospace Engineering from Georgia Tech
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2026.01]</span>
          Submitted "Allocating Corrective Control to Mitigate Multi-agent Safety Violations Under Private Preferences" to IEEE RA-L
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2025.03]</span>
          Passed qualifying exam
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2024.01]</span>
          Co-authored paper on lunar regolith truss structures at AIAA SCITECH 2024
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2023.08]</span>
          Started PhD in Robotics at Georgia Tech
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2023.08]</span>
          Completed 3 years as Senior Engineer at Physical Sciences, Inc.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2020.05]</span>
          Graduated BS Aeronautical Engineering from RPI, Cum Laude
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="news-date text-amber">[2020]</span>
          Published additive manufacturing research in J. Micro and Nano-Manufacturing
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-name {
    font-size: 3rem;
    text-shadow: var(--glow-lg);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-typing {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .news-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .news-list li {
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(var(--primary-rgb), 0.08);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .news-date {
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
  }

  .explainer p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cbf-details {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .cbf-details summary {
    color: var(--amber);
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .cbf-details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .cbf-details summary::before {
    content: '▸ ';
  }

  .cbf-details[open] summary::before {
    content: '▾ ';
  }

  .details-content {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .details-content p {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .details-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .mobile-only {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem;
    }

    .hero-name {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .desktop-only {
      display: none;
    }

    .mobile-only {
      display: inline;
    }
  }
</style>
